<article class="border-l-4 border-[hsl(24,95%,53%)] pl-6">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-1">June 30, 2026</h2>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-4">Shipped <code>/horse-breeding-software</code> as page A3 of the 12-page LP cluster plan. Targets the "horse breeding software" / "equine breeding software" / "mare management software" / "stallion booking software" query family without cannibalizing <code>/compare/best-horse-breeding-software</code> (buyer's guide intent) or <code>/compare/best-dog-breeding-software</code> (different species).</p>

  <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong>Why.</strong> Strategy doc (<code>UNIFIED-STRATEGY-2026-06.md</code>) called out species-vertical landing pages as a Cluster A gap. Horse breeders searching "horse breeding software" or "mare management software" had no direct product LP — only the comparison page and the species hub, neither of which converts on commercial intent. A3 closes the gap.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>What the page is.</strong> A species-specific, equine-vocabulary LP for working horse breeders. Mirrors the dog and cat sibling pages' structure (breadcrumb, hero + dual CTA, TL;DR aside, workflow pill strip, eight-point "what changes when you go from spreadsheet to system" rubric, stallion-side section, multi-discipline section, honest-scope band, pricing CTA, FAQ, learn-more, final CTA, sticky mobile CTA, RelatedWorkflows). Equine vocabulary throughout: mare, stallion, foal, in-foal, live cover, AI cooled, AI frozen, embryo transfer, breeding session, covering, semen inventory, foaling, IgG, recipient mare. Zero puppy/whelp language per cluster discipline rule 3 and the equine voice memory rule.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Schema.</strong> SoftwareApplication JSON-LD on-page with <code>audience.audienceType=Horse Breeders</code> per the A3 brief and an equine-specific <code>featureList</code> (mare cycle tracking, breeding session log across methods, stallion bookings, semen inventory, registry-aware records for AQHA/Jockey Club/USEF/Warmblood). FAQPage and BreadcrumbList ride through BaseLayout's <code>faqs</code> + <code>breadcrumbs</code> props (auto-emitted). No Article (this is a product LP, not editorial).
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Outbound links from the new page</strong> satisfy the per-page contract in the plan: <code>/pricing</code>, <code>/horses</code>, <code>/compare/best-horse-breeding-software</code>, <code>/breeder-management-software</code> (A1 sibling, already shipped), <code>/tools/coefficient-of-inbreeding-calculator</code> (B2, not yet shipped — planned broken-link debt that resolves on Day 6 per the plan), <code>/services/equine-boarding/lexington-ky</code> (reciprocal link back to the geo page per the equine-geo project), and <code>/trust</code>. The COI calculator link is intentional broken-link debt per the plan's daily execution sequence.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Anti-cannibalization checks</strong> (cluster discipline rule 1): H1 is "Horse Breeding Software for Working Farms" — does not contain "best ... software" or any dog-page exact-match term. Page does not include the cross-tool comparison table from <code>/compare</code>. Links OUT to <code>/compare/best-horse-breeding-software</code> as the buyer's-guide handoff in the TL;DR.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Trust posture compliance.</strong> Honest-scope section explicitly lists what BreederHQ does not do for horses (does not perform ET/AI procedures, does not provide veterinary services, does not file registry submissions, does not verify/vet/vouch for breeders) and links to <code>/trust</code> as "Identity and Credentials" per the legally-locked posture. No "verified breeder" claims anywhere on the page.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Equine voice compliance</strong> (memory rule on equine pages): operations- and discipline-aware framing throughout (1,000-pound athletes, breeding shed, foaling stall, registry deadline, vet schedule), discipline-respectful (sport horse, ranch, Thoroughbred hobby, Friesian frozen-semen import, AQHA, Warmblood, USEF), and zero pet-boarding voice. The "tool does not impose a workflow" section addresses the discipline-spread directly.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>9-species honesty.</strong> Horses are explicitly framed as one of nine public species in the same account. The cross-species framing in the multi-discipline section ("a sport horse breeder who also runs a small kennel, a ranch with cattle and quarter horses, a goat dairy with a couple of riding horses") points at the platform's actual cross-sell advantage. No stealth framing, no "free tier" language — "14-day free trial" everywhere, with <code>FOUNDER50</code> mentioned in both the pricing band and the FAQ.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>What is next per the plan.</strong> Day-4 ships A4 <code>/breeder-crm</code>. Then Cluster B (B1 <code>/litter-management</code>, B2 <code>/tools/coefficient-of-inbreeding-calculator</code>) and Cluster C (the five <code>/compare/[competitor]-alternative</code> pages). After Week 1, the cross-cluster reciprocal-link audit sweeps additional inbound links from <code>/pricing</code>, <code>/horses</code>, <code>/compare/best-horse-breeding-software</code>, and the dog comparison page.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Success criteria at 4 weeks.</strong> GSC: any impressions on "horse breeding software" or "mare management software" head terms (current baseline: zero). Striking-distance position (4-20) within 8 weeks. If neither moves, the bottleneck is domain authority, not page-level relevance, and the next lever is backlinks rather than more pages.
    </p>
  </div>
